Quick Estimate.value: Quick Estimate (rough quote for the customer — dial in later)

Use this tab for a fast, rough estimate based on your saved Assumptions (fuel, miles per gallon, fixed overhead, driver pay, margin, risk, minimum charge). This excludes detailed accessorial charges. If something miscellaneous applies, enter it in 'Other (flat $ add-on)'.
Inputs you typically get from the shipper
Diesel price override (leave 0 to use Assumptions)
Target margin override (leave blank to use Assumptions)
Contingency percent (extras + risk) override (leave blank to use Assumptions)
="Rough estimate: "&TEXT(E46,"$#,##0")&" | Loaded: "&TEXT($B$12,"#,##0")&" mi | Deadhead: "&TEXT($B$13,"#,##0")&" mi | Weight: "&TEXT($B$11,"#,##0")&" lb | Equip: "&$B$10
Market reference rate per loaded mile (Rate Cards)
Market linehaul (loaded miles × market rate, with minimum)
Market-based estimate (market linehaul + market fuel surcharge) × (1+contingency)
Estimate after minimum (choose higher of cost-based vs market-based)

README.value:
1) Enter blue cells on 'Load Input' (miles, dates, accessorial quantities, fees).
2) Update operating assumptions (fuel price, miles per gallon, driver pay, fixed costs) on 'Assumptions'.
3) Optional: maintain default accessorial fees in 'Accessorials' and reference lane rates in 'Rate Cards'.
4) Use 'Pricing Summary' for final quote, justification narrative, and internal cost breakdown.
Blue text = inputs. Green text = linked values. Black text = formulas. Yellow fill = update frequently.

Assumptions.value: Stop time per pickup and delivery
Diesel exhaust fluid cost per gallon
Diesel exhaust fluid gallons per 1,000 miles
Driver pay and fixed cost assumptions
Owner-operator (no separate wage); Dollars per mile; Dollars per hour; Percent of linehaul
Target margin on price; Target markup on cost

Enter actual dollars in quantity field

Rate Cards.value: Market reference rates (optional; edit blue cells)
General hotshot flatbed; minimum protects deadhead
Lowboy/equipment: slower routing + higher securement risk

Higher operating cost; dock time; lane-dependent backhaul
Expedite style, small payload, premium flexibility

Recommended price before broker and card fees

Blank 6 Read Me.value: 1) Go to the Blank 6 Assumptions sheet and set your default operating assumptions (fuel price, fuel economy, variable cost per mile, fixed cost per day, overhead, and target profit margin).
2) Go to the Blank 6 Rate Card sheet and set your default base rate per loaded mile and minimum linehaul for each equipment type you run.
3) Enter each load on the Blank 6 Loads sheet (loaded miles, deadhead miles, accessorial fees, and any load-specific overrides like fuel price or base rate).
4) Review the calculated results on the right side of the Blank 6 Loads sheet: market-based price, cost-based recommended price, expected profit, and profit margin.
5) Use the Blank 6 Load Quote sheet to select a Load ID and get a clean quote breakdown you can copy into an email or send to a customer/broker.
- Blue cells are intended for user input.
- This section is included from Blank 6 as a separate model tab set.

Blank 6 Assumptions.value: Base fuel price included in base rate (dollars per gallon)

Fixed cost per day (dollars per day)
